Level 822 is the 823<sup>rd</sup> level of the Backrooms.<div class="blurquote-noperson blurquote-noborder" style="margin:1em;">{{Blurquote|image=822822822.jpeg|quote-text=<br> The dark sky is full of lofty mountains, and everything is bleak and cold. I feel more lonely in here. <br><br>}}
{{Blurimage|file=822822822.jpeg|caption=The magnificent and boundless mountains.}}
==Description==
'''Level 822''' is a mountainous region of immense size, characterized by numerous peaks and deep canyons that form the majority of its landscape. The mountains rise in layers, with steep walls and jagged peaks. The mountain range seems to go on, stretching in all directions to a dark, impenetrable horizon. The actual size of the range has yet to be determined, and any attempts to cross or map its boundaries have failed.

A constant, monotonous, grayish darkness fills the level. The sky is covered by heavy, unmoving and unchanging clouds made up of an unfamiliar dark substance. The light emitted is very weak. It is a constant glow, with no signs of day and night, and the little light that seeks its way through the canopy of clouds is absorbed into the near nonreflective rock that makes up 822's environment.

The materials that make up the mountain are mainly dry loess or dark-colored rocks with rough surface textures and grayscale colors. Because of the less-than-ideal environment, native vegetation is almost unseen in this level, and only several twisted, dark-colored low mosses or drought-resistant ferns can be found in sheltered and humid crevices or narrow valley bottoms. <div class="blurquote-noperson blurquote-noborder" style="margin:1em;">{{Blurquote|image=822822822.jpeg|quote-text=<br>Dust obscures the sky, miasma engulfs the road, and loneliness eats at one's bones. Eerie sounds echo in the empty valley, hindering one's vision.<br><br>}}
{{Blurimage|file=822822822a.jpeg|caption=Another picture of the level.}}Within the mountains and canyons of this level, the wind can grow violent. Since the soil on '''Level 822''' is extremely loose, it is easy when the wind blows for it to kick up into large dirt storms, reducing visibility and attaching to one's clothes. Long-term inhalation can easily lead to pneumoconiosis, which has adverse effects. It is recommended one finds shelter during these storms. The level's hillside structure is unstable and landslide prone, and because of the wind, rockfalls are frequent even without human intervention.


The haze, containing an unknown composition, with a substantial feeling, is a common phenomenon in this level. It is not evenly distributed, but slowly flows, often floating at the bottom of the valley, on the mountainside pass, or between the peaks. These mists greatly hinder the vision, blurring the distant mountains into hazy gray silhouettes, making it difficult for wanderers to see the details of the terrain ahead when traveling, increasing the risk of getting lost.

In '''Level 822''', the available resources are extremely scarce, as drinkable water supplies are rare. Occasionally, one can find slow, icy, and tiny drops of water seeping out from deep in shaded rock crevices, but it is tough to collect them. [[Object 1|Almond Water]] or other supplies commonly found in the Backrooms are almost impossible to obtain naturally in the mountain range. Wanderers must rely on the supplies they bring when they enter, or in extremely rare cases, find trace amounts of supplies left behind by previous wanderers in some hard-to-reach, hidden corners that may have been weathered. Food sources are also scarce, as there are no stable resources.

Spending extended periods in '''Level 822''' will have a lasting effect on the wanderer's mental state. The extreme monotony of the environment, the permanent dimness of light, the severely limited field of vision, and the lack of resources all combine to create a deep, lingering sense of loneliness and isolation. The height of the mountain and the sheer scale of the environment can easily induce a sense of insignificance and helplessness.

There are some inexplicable phenomena in the level's environment. The wind howls between the mountains, either low and whimpering or sharp and piercing, but its source and direction are often confusing. Occasionally, one can hear the dull sound of falling rocks from a distance, but the source of it is often impossible to locate, and there seems to be no actual geological activity corresponding to it. It is easy to get confused about the sense of direction when navigating. Even if one uses tools such as a compass, their reliability will be affected by unknown interference. The landform features in some areas are highly repetitive, making positioning and path identification extremely difficult.

==Phenomena==
<div style="background-color:#D9CAB3; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #B5A569; border-radius: 3px"><div class="mw-customtoggle-first">'''The Barrier'''</div><div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-first">
'''Level 822''' has a phenomenon known as "The Barrier". When gazing at a mountain in the distance, the wanderer's sense of actual length and size will be constantly and irregularly misjudged.

The towering mountains will appear to be close to the wanderer, but the distance the wanderer feels is far greater than the actual distance. On the contrary, the nearby cliffs will sometimes expand suddenly and sometimes collapse beyond the naked eye.

This severe confusion in perception of scale and space is uncontrollable and occurs randomly, forcing one to endure futile physical exertion. The frequent mental shocks can easily lead to deep loss, mental exhaustion, collapse, and ultimately death from physical exhaustion.</div></div>

<div style="background-color:#D9CAB3; color: black; margin:1em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #B5A569; border-radius: 3px"><div class="mw-customtoggle-second">'''Unstable Geological Shifting'''</div><div class="mw-collapsible mw-collapsed" id="mw-customcollapsible-second">The mountains of '''Level 822''' are slowly and always moving. The rolling ridges and deep chasms sometimes undergo slow, imperceptible changes.
The low hum of rock friction will appear with this change. A previously safe pathway may quietly close, shift, change, or even disappear, forcing one to constantly face unpredictable and unfamiliar dangers.</div></div>

==Addendum==
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">Found Note</span><br><center>'''''There is No Future'''''<br><br></center>
I shuttled through the valleys and wandered among the mountains. The outlines of them were blurred in the eternal twilight, and the rock layers were exposed like forgotten bones. The wind eroded them and also my remaining warmth. The ground cracked open like some kind of omen.

I often wonder: How limited is one's knowledge of the future? I once believed that my footsteps could measure the world, but now my will for that has disappeared. My self-awareness has collapsed, and the end is approaching - this is not a declaration, but an acceptance of absurdity.

This is pure despair, a kind of abandoned loneliness. In the blurred mountain outline, I question: "Is this real? Or is everything an illusion, so that I can survive in this chaos?". I am willing to succumb to fear because death makes pain insignificant.

There is no logic of redemption here. As the dust filled my throat, I finally realized: what we struggled with, what we feared, what we tried to hold on to, was nothing but nothing. And this dead mountain range will eventually witness how we are weathered into dust.
<div class="onlylight"><span style="font-family:Rubik Glitch; background: -webkit-linear-gradient(#323232, #323232); -webkit-background-clip: text; webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom 8px; margin-right: -8px;">Everything we witnessed was in the Backrooms...</span></div><div class="onlydark"><span style="font-family:Rubik Glitch; background: -webkit-linear-gradient(#C0C0C0, #C0C0C0); -webkit-background-clip: text; webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom -8px;">Everything we witnessed was in the Backrooms...</span></div></div>
==Entities==
There are no entities in '''Level 822''' due to the instability of the level.

== Colonies and Outposts ==
Due to the almost boundless environment of this floor, wanderers will rarely meet each other, making colonies and outposts hard to form.

==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
*Running and tripping in [[Level 908]] will lead one here.
*Walk along a dusty street in [[Level 11]] towards a certain location to enter this level.
*A light-colored area in [[Level 46]] will bring one here.
===Exits===
*Entering "The Oasis" will lead to [[Level 13]].
*Entering a small chapel then leaving will lead to [[Level 566]].
